servings: 2
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Leave to the side until ready to serve.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Lower the heat to medium.

Stir the cooked rice, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @korma curry paste{50%g} and @peas{120%g} into the pork until well combined.

Stir the @mango chutney{40%g} through your pilaf.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little dry.

When ready, share the pork pilaf between your #bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}.

Finish with a sprinkle of the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} for those who'd like them. Enjoy!

